race.comment: HYDROGEN POWER (2) stepped up to 1600m at Tatura and was beaten a whisker from the pace in stronger grade. Carries more weight but winning rider Yendall is reunited and the gelding presents on a 7-day return. Is likely to control the race and will take plenty of stopping. WEATHER DELAY (3) is third-up and has more to give over the longer journey. He's won here over this distance and should enjoy the run of the race. Hurdle stays aboard. I'LLBETHERE (1) was heavily bet when winning his Maiden over a mile at Donald. He's in a smart barn and fitter will bet every chance to take the next step. KOKONOTSU (4) is hard to catch but has the ability and should be around the mark. RIPPER (5) has been beaten less than a length his last two and is back in grade.
